  "prompt": "What does \"subject to availability\" mean?",
  "response": "\"Subject to availability\" is a phrase commonly used to indicate that the provision of a product, service, or some other item is dependent on whether it is obtainable or accessible at the time it is needed or requested. In other words, it means that the item in question is not guaranteed and its fulfillment depends on its availability at the specific time. This term is often used in the travel and hospitality industry, where reservations and bookings are made based on the availability of rooms, flights, or other services.",
